.TH "WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc" "JS" "July 26, 2024" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc \- WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc
extension
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc\f[B]\f[R] extension is
part of the WebGL API and exposes four \c
.UR https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PVRTC
PVRTC compressed texture formats
.UE \c
\&.
.PP
Compressed textures reduce the amount of memory needed to store a
texture on the GPU, allowing for higher resolution textures or more of
the same resolution textures.
.PP
WebGL extensions are available using the
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.getExtension()\f[R] method.
For more information, see also Using Extensions in the WebGL tutorial.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] PVRTC is typically only available on mobile devices with
PowerVR chipsets.
It is used in all generations of the iPhone, iPod Touch and iPad and
supported on certain Android devices that use a PowerVR GPU.
.PP
This extension is available to both, WebGL1 and WebGL2 contexts.
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] On iOS devices, this extension is named
\f[CR]WEBKIT_WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc\f[R].
.RE
.SH CONSTANTS
The compressed texture formats are exposed by four constants and can be
used in two functions: \f[CR]compressedTexImage2D()\f[R] (where the
\f[CR]height\f[R] and \f[CR]width\f[R] parameters must be powers of 2)
and \f[CR]compressedTexSubImage2D()\f[R] (where the height and width
parameters must equal the current values of the existing texture and the
\f[CR]xoffset\f[R] and \f[CR]yoffset\f[R] parameters must be 0).
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG\f[R]
RGB compression in 4\-bit mode.
One block for each 4×4 pixels.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG\f[R]
RGBA compression in 4\-bit mode.
One block for each 4×4 pixels.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG\f[R]
RGB compression in 2\-bit mode.
One block for each 8×4 pixels.
.TP
\f[B]ext.COMPRESSED_RGBA_PVRTC_2BPPV1_IMG\f[R]
RGBA compression in 2\-bit mode.
One block for each 8×4 pixels.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] ext = gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc\[dq]);

\f[B]const\f[R] texture = gl.createTexture();
gl.bindTexture(gl.TEXTURE_2D, texture);

gl.compressedTexImage2D(
  gl.TEXTURE_2D,
  0,
  ext.COMPRESSED_RGB_PVRTC_4BPPV1_IMG,
  512,
  512,
  0,
  textureData,
);
.EE
